  01 Nov 2004; Henrik Brix Andersen <brix@gentoo.org>
  hostap-driver-0.1.1.ebuild, hostap-driver-0.1.2-r1.ebuild,
  hostap-driver-0.1.2-r2.ebuild, hostap-driver-0.1.2.ebuild,
  hostap-driver-0.1.3.ebuild, hostap-driver-0.2.4.ebuild,
  hostap-driver-0.2.5.ebuild:
  Use tc-getCC() from toolchain-funcs.eclass, fixes bug #69281.

  26 Oct 2004; Henrik Brix Andersen <brix@gentoo.org>
  hostap-driver-0.2.5.ebuild:
  Do not substitute gcc in the Makefile. Hopefully fixes bug #68537.

*hostap-driver-0.2.5 (25 Oct 2004)

  25 Oct 2004; Henrik Brix Andersen <brix@gentoo.org>
  +hostap-driver-0.2.5.ebuild:
  Version bump. Cleaned up the ebuild beyond recognition, dropped hostap-* USE
  flags since the package no longer supports building only some of the modules.

*hostap-driver-0.2.4 (14 Sep 2004)

  14 Sep 2004; Henrik Brix Andersen <brix@gentoo.org>
  +hostap-driver-0.2.4.ebuild:
  Bump. Ebuild by latexer@gentoo.org.

  12 Aug 2004; Michael Hanselmann <hansmi@gentoo.org>
  hostap-driver-0.1.2-r2.ebuild:
  Added to ~ppc.

  09 Aug 2004; Peter Johanson <latexer@gentoo.org> hostap-driver-0.1.1.ebuild,
  hostap-driver-0.1.2-r1.ebuild, hostap-driver-0.1.2-r2.ebuild,
  hostap-driver-0.1.2.ebuild, hostap-driver-0.1.3.ebuild:
  Remove RDEPEND to block against hostap, as that's getting removed.

  01 Jun 2004; Peter Johanson <latexer@gentoo.org> hostap-driver-0.1.3.ebuild:
  Mark 0.1.3 stable on x86.

  27 Apr 2004; Aron Griffis <agriffis@gentoo.org>
  hostap-driver-0.1.2-r2.ebuild, hostap-driver-0.1.3.ebuild:
  Add inherit eutils

  09 Feb 2004; Peter Johanson <latexer@gentoo.org>
  hostap-driver-0.1.2-r1.ebuild:
  Fixed version detection for pcmcia-cs versions that have a revision number.
  (Thanks again to brix@gimp.org)

*hostap-driver-0.1.3 (09 Feb 2004)

  09 Feb 2004; Wolfram Schlich <wschlich@gentoo.org>
  hostap-driver-0.1.3.ebuild, files/hostap-driver-0.1.3.firmware.diff.bz2:
  Version bump, ebuild fixes/changes

*hostap-driver-0.1.2-r2 (07 Feb 2004)

  07 Feb 2004; Peter Johanson <latexer@gentoo.org> metadata.xml,
  hostap-driver-0.1.2-r2.ebuild:
  Major cleanup. Uses new pcmcia.eclass and handles 2.6 kernels if you disable
  sandbox. Added myself to the metadata.xml

*hostap-driver-0.1.2-r1 (03 Jan 2004)

